# ***challenge.json.sample is the challenge information, rsa_signer_key.json is the rsa keys file, this is simulated, the real one must be initiated by the computing machine***
unc extensions create-challenge-rsa fd09e7537ee95fd2e7b78ee0a2b10bb9db4ebe65dc94802ce420c94ebb25bc43 use-file ~/keys/challenge.json.sample without-init-call network-config custom sign-with-access-key-file ~/keys/rsa_signer_key.json send batch_register.json.sample Register miner configuration information, the field power default unit is Tera which is 10.pow(12) [ { "miner_id": "miner0", "public_key": "rsa2048:", "power": 100, "sn": "serial number here c0", "bus_id": "bus info c0", "p2key": "p2keys1 c0" }, { "miner_id": "miner1", "public_key": "rsa2048:", "power": 200, "sn": "serial number here c1", "bus_id": "bus info c1", "p2key": "p2keys1 c1" }, { "miner_id": "miner2", "public_key": "rsa2048:", "power": 300, "sn": "serial number here c2", "bus_id": "bus info c2", "p2key": "p2keys1 c2" }
] challenge.json.sample Activate computing power and initiate challenge configuration information { "public_key": "rsa2048:", "challenge_key": "ed25519:8FhzmFG24qXxJ9BJLHTxwhxYY4yu4NV8YPxtksmC86Nv"
} rsa_signer_key.json The challenge is initiated using the rsa2048 keys signature file { "account_id": "miner-test1", "public_key": "rsa2048:", "private_key": "rsa2048:"
}
